Javacript Execution Context [JEC]:
{} global-EC -this(window object)

- Global EC
- Function EC
- Eval EC [property of global object]

||js code executes in 2 phases||

1. memory creation phase
2. execution phase

//understnading w code:

<!-- let val1 : 10
let val2 : 5
function add(n, m){
    let total = n+m
    return total
}
let result1 = add(val1, val2)
let result2 = add(10,2) -->

firstly:
----Memory phase----
val1, val2 = undefined |
add = function's definition
result1, result2 = undefined

----Execution phase----
val1, val2 = 10, 5
add [exection context i.e. new variable environment & execution thread]
::
-MP- [val1, val2, total] and -EP- [num1=10, num2=5, total=15] again
total returned to |GLOBAL EXECUTION CONTEXT|

then DELETE;

Secondly:
new variable environment+ thread
result2::
again repeat!!
total returned to |GLOBAL EXECUTION CONTEXT|

---

            CALLSTACK:

If in Global-EC we have many function and we call then one-after-another
without returning it so it creates a stack! ---Follows LIFO---

eg:
function one(){
console.log("one")
}
function two(){
console.log("two")
}
function three(){
console.log("three")
}

one()
two()
three()
